<div class="question-card" id="card-14" data-qid="14" data-type="multi" data-choose="2">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 15</span>
    <span class="q-tag multi">Choose 2</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      What are two characteristics of IP? (Choose two.)
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-14">
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">retransmits packets if errors occur</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">guarantees delivery of packets</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">does not require a dedicated end-to-end connection</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">operates independently of the network media</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="4">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">E</span>
        <span class="opt-text">re-assembles out of order packets into the correct order at the receiver end</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn multi-pending" id="submit-14" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
      
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-14">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-14"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        The Internet Protocol (IP) is a connectionless, best effort protocol. This means that IP requires no end-to-end connection nor does it guarantee delivery of packets. IP is also media independent, which means it operates independently of the network media carrying the packets.
      </div>
    </div>
